SP  - 407
EP  - 432
VL  - 72
IS  - 2
KW  - Reputation
KW  - imperfect monitoring
KW  - repeated games
KW  - commitment
KW  - Stackelberg types
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2004.00496.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We study the long-run sustainability of reputations in games with imperfect public monitoring. It is impossible to maintain a permanent reputation for playing a strategy that does not play an equilibrium of the game without uncertainty about types. Thus, a player cannot indefinitely sustain a reputation for noncredible behavior in the presence of imperfect monitoring.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Information in Securities Markets: Kyle Meets Glosten and Milgrom
AU  - Back, Kerry
AU  - Baruch, Shmuel
Y1  - 2004/03/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/03/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2004.00497.x
